        <name>BT_BYTES_LIST_LE16</name>
        <param><defname>_v</defname></param>
        <initializer>	(((_v) &gt;&gt;  0) &amp; 0xFFU),     \
	(((_v) &gt;&gt;  8) &amp; 0xFFU)      \</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Encode 16-bit value into array values in little-endian format. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Helper macro to encode 16-bit values into comma separated values.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para><computeroutput>_v</computeroutput> is evaluated 2 times.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>_v</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>16-bit integer in host endianness.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>The comma separated values for the 16-bit value. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
